let the given triangle be - 
<img src="https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/5eb3b4f0-4087-4170-a887-e64e5ae9a95e_1655084796.5711522.png" height = 400>


there may be two case either go from top or from bottom. we can use recursive approach in the top by deciding whether we should take the jth element or j+1 element in the i+1 row . this will create the whole tree structure of triangle and then we will return the min element at the end. we can keep on adding all the min sum which will be the answer.(time limit is exceeding in this case).

if we go from bottom approach we can do using for loops, the idea is **For any ith row, we will start traversing each jth element and we will add current jth element with minimum value of j and j+1 element of (i+1) row.**
Note - since we need to consider the row below it, we are going to start from second last row.
