Doing normal dfs will ensure that you hit the time limit. If you go through a simple example you will see that certain path will be reprocessed. It is best to save the best sum for each node and abort if you encounter the same path.
This solution does not attempt to lower space to n, it is however very easy to follow and runs quickly.

The idea is simple:

1. Use DFS to get to the bottom of the triangle.
2. At each node, save the best sum.
3. The best sum is calculated as: currentNode + min(leftChild, rightChild)
4. The base case should return 0 as the sum, if you are at the last level, the left and right child will return 0. As such the best sum will simply be the currentNode.
```
class Solution {        

    int memoized[][];

    public int minimumTotal(List<List<Integer>> triangle) {
        memoized = new int[triangle.size()][triangle.size()];

        // FILL ALL ELEMENTS WITH DEFAULT TO CHECK IF IT HAS BEEN POPULATED
        for (int[] row : memoized) {
            Arrays.fill(row, Integer.MIN_VALUE);
        }

        return minimumTotal(triangle, 0, 0);
    }

    public int minimumTotal(List<List<Integer>> triangle, int level, int col) {
        // BASE CASE - NO MORE ROWS TO PROCESS, RETURN 0 SIZE THE BEST SUM AFTER THE LAST ROW IS 0
        if (level == triangle.size()) {
            return 0;
        }

        // IF WE PROCESSED THIS COMBO BEFORE, RETURN THE BEST RECORDED SUM
        if (memoized[level][col] != Integer.MIN_VALUE) {
            return memoized[level][col];
        }

        final List<Integer> nums = triangle.get(level);
        int num = nums.get(col);

        // WE CAN GO LEFT OR RIGHT, NODES HAVE TO BE ADJACENT
        int leftSum = minimumTotal(triangle, level + 1, col);
        int rightSum = minimumTotal(triangle, level + 1, col + 1);

        // TAKE THE BEST OF THE LEFT OR RIGHT AND ADD THE CURRENT NODE
        int currentBestSum = num + Math.min(leftSum, rightSum);

        // SAVE THIS RESULT IN CASE WE WANT TO PROCESS THIS TREE AGAIN
        memoized[level][col] = currentBestSum;

        return currentBestSum;
    }
}
```

