# Approach
Goigng from bottom to the top we will choose the most optimal way to get from the previous layer to the current. We can get to the current cell from two cells on the previous layer - calculate both those ways and choose the minimum. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(N)$$
Where ***N*** is the number of all cells in the triangle.
- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
func minimumTotal(triangle [][]int) int {
    for i := len(triangle) - 2; i >= 0; i-- {
        for j := 0; j < len(triangle[i]); j++ {
           triangle[i][j] += min(triangle[i+1][j], triangle[i+1][j + 1])
        }
    }

    return triangle[0][0]
}

func min(a,b int) int {
    if a < b {
        return a
    }
    return b
}

