solutions.content:
While going down you decide which path to take on the basis of what was the min cost in the upper paths.
We do reverse of this, we go down->up

while doing this:
1. check which path costs min, coming up from cell just below it traingle[i+1][j] or coming from cell diagonally below current cell triangle[i+1][j+1] find optimal path and store that ans for current cell.
2. While going up keep storing min path for each cell and the topmost cell will eventually have the ans .
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumTotal(vector<vector<int>>& triangle) {

        int n=triangle.size();


        for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
            int m=triangle[i].size();//number of cols in each row of triangle matrix
            for(int j=m-1;j>=0;j--){
                triangle[i][j]+=min(triangle[i+1][j],triangle[i+1][j+1]);
                //min cost from cell just below it or diagonally below it 
            }
        }

        return triangle[0][0]; //ans 
    }
};
```

